@startuml sequence_kafka_events
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam sequenceArrowColor #333333

title Sequence Diagram: Async Event Processing via Kafka (MVP)

participant RTB as "RTB Service"
participant Kafka as "Kafka\nBroker"
participant Analytics as "Analytics\nConsumer"
participant Financial as "Financial\nConsumer"
participant TimeSeries as "TimeSeries DB\n(InfluxDB)"
participant PG as "PostgreSQL\nMaster"

autonumber

== Event Publishing (Non-blocking) ==

note over RTB
  After sending BidResponse to DSP
  (typically 50-100ms after auction)
end note

RTB -> Kafka: PublishEvent()\nimpression.recorded\n{\n  event_id: "evt-abc123",\n  campaign_id: "camp-789",\n  price: 550,\n  user_id: "user-123",\n  timestamp: now()\n}

activate Kafka
note over Kafka
  Partitioning key: campaign_id
  Ensures ordering within campaign
  
  Message enqueued immediately
  Fire-and-forget (non-blocking)
  Latency: ~1ms
end note

note over RTB
  RTB doesn't wait for ACK
  Response already sent to DSP!
  Event publishing is background task
end note
deactivate RTB

== Topic Partitioning ==

Kafka -> Kafka: Determine partition\npartition = hash(campaign_id) % 10\nIn this case: partition 9

note over Kafka
  10 partitions total
  Campaigns 9,19,29,... → partition 9
  Allows parallel consumption
  Ordering guaranteed per partition
end note

== Analytics Consumer Group ==

note over Kafka
  Consumer group: analytics-impressions
  Rebalance: each partition → one consumer
end note

Kafka -> Analytics: Fetch messages\nfrom partition 9\n(batch: up to 100 messages)

activate Analytics

note over Analytics
  Processing latency: OK up to 500ms
  Purpose: aggregation + dashboards
  Not time-critical
end note

Analytics -> Analytics: Parse JSON\nimpression.recorded

Analytics -> Analytics: Aggregate statistics\nfor this time window:\n{\n  campaign_id: "camp-789",\n  date: "2026-06-22",\n  impressions: +1,\n  clicks: (later in clicks topic),\n  spend_cents: +550\n}

note over Analytics
  Update in-memory counters
  Periodically flush to DB (e.g., every 1 min)
end note

Analytics -> TimeSeries: WriteMetrics()\nmetric: impressions\ntags: {campaign: camp-789, date: 2026-06-22}\nvalue: +1

activate TimeSeries
TimeSeries -> TimeSeries: Append to time series
note over TimeSeries
  InfluxDB stores metrics
  Used for dashboards
  Real-time analytics
end note
TimeSeries --> Analytics: ✓ OK (100ms)
deactivate TimeSeries

Analytics -> Kafka: CommitOffset()\noffset: message #N

note over Kafka
  Offset stored in Kafka
  If consumer restarts:
  - Resume from last offset
  - No reprocessing ✅
end note

Kafka --> Analytics: ✓ Committed
deactivate Analytics

== Financial Consumer Group ==

note over Kafka
  Consumer group: financial-impressions
  Different consumer group reads same messages!
  Independent offset tracking
end note

Kafka -> Financial: Fetch messages\nfrom partition 9\n(batch: up to 50 messages)

activate Financial

note over Financial
  Processing latency: must be <1s
  Purpose: budget tracking + enforcement
  Time-sensitive (payment-related)
  
  REQUIREMENT: Exactly-once processing
end note

Financial -> Financial: Parse JSON\nimpression.recorded

Financial -> Financial: Check deduplication\nHave we seen event_id before?
note over Financial
  Check in-memory dedup cache
  + check processed_events table
  
  Ensures idempotency
  Safe to retry this event
end note

alt Event_id not seen before
  
  Financial -> PG: BEGIN TRANSACTION
  
  activate PG
  note over PG
    Transactional writes
    Ensures consistency
  end note
  
  Financial -> PG: INSERT processed_events\n(event_id, campaign_id, timestamp)
  note over PG
    Deduplication record
    Prevents reprocessing if consumer restarts
  end note
  
  Financial -> PG: UPDATE campaigns\nSET spent_today_cents = spent_today_cents + 550\nWHERE id = 'camp-789'
  
  Financial -> PG: SELECT spent_today_cents, daily_budget_cents\nFROM campaigns\nWHERE id = 'camp-789'
  
  activate PG
  note over PG
    spending_now: 455000 cents
    daily_budget: 500000 cents
    remaining: 45000 cents
  end note
  PG --> Financial: {spent: 455000, budget: 500000}
  deactivate PG
  
  alt spent >= budget
    Financial -> PG: UPDATE campaigns\nSET is_paused = true\nWHERE id = 'camp-789'
    
    note over Financial
      Campaign paused!
      Alert sent to advertiser
      No more ads will be shown
    end note
  end
  
  Financial -> PG: COMMIT TRANSACTION
  deactivate PG
  
  note over Financial
    Transaction complete
    All-or-nothing guarantee ✅
  end note
  
else Event_id already processed
  
  note over Financial
    We've seen this event before
    Skip processing (idempotent)
    But still commit offset
  end note
  
end

Financial -> Kafka: CommitOffset()\noffset: message #N

Kafka --> Financial: ✓ Committed
deactivate Financial

== Timeline Visualization ==

note over RTB, PG
  
  === Timeline Example ===
  
  14:30:00.000 - Impression served to user
  14:30:00.050 - BidResponse sent to DSP ✓
  14:30:00.051 - impression.recorded event published to Kafka
  
  14:30:00.100 - Analytics consumer picks up event
  14:30:00.150 - Analytics processes & writes to TimeSeries
  
  14:30:00.100 - Financial consumer picks up event
  14:30:00.200 - Financial updates budget ledger
  
  === Key Points ===
  
  • RTB path: 50ms (critical) ✓
  • Kafka publish: 1ms (non-blocking) ✓
  • Analytics: 100-500ms OK ✓
  • Financial: 100ms OK (<1s requirement) ✓
  • Ordering: guaranteed per partition (campaign_id) ✓
  • Deduplication: event_id ensures exactly-once ✓
  
end note

== Failure Scenarios ==

note over Kafka
  
  === Kafka Broker Down ===
  • RTB service: local queue (persist to disk)
  • Analytics: paused (resume when back)
  • Financial: paused (resume when back)
  • No data loss (backlog persists)
  
  === Consumer Crash ===
  • Kafka rebalances partitions
  • Another consumer takes over
  • Resume from last committed offset
  • No reprocessing (offset tracking)
  
  === Duplicate Event ===
  • Consumer retries (at-least-once)
  • event_id deduplication prevents double-charging ✓
  
end note

@enduml
